ODBC - Independent connector 
JDBC - Mysql connection with SqlDeveloper/Eclipse 
	https://oracle-base.com/articles/mysql/mysql-connections-in-sql-developer#downloads

1. Download the latest "JDBC Driver for MySQL (Connector/J)" from here. 
   Click the "Download" link next to the "JDBC Driver for MySQL (Connector/J)", then select the platform independent version and download the zip file.
2. Unzip the connector. The resulting directory contains a "mysql-connector-java-5.1.30-bin.jar" file.
3. Open SQL Developer and navigate to "Tools > Preferences > Database > Third Party JDBC Driver".
4. Click the "Add Entry..." button and highlight the "mysql-connector-java-5.1.30-bin.jar" file and click the "Select" button.
5. Click the "OK" button to exit the "Preferences" dialog.
6. When you create a new connection, you will notice a "MySQL" tab has now appeared. Enter the connection details and test the connection.
	
Hibernate 4.0	